yas [and] a hundred kalpas I have gathered, [in the form of] gift[s], moral, powers [and] knowledge, endless merit(s).</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>401</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a8"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>231</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1969"/><citedRange>261</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:kolver1965"/><citedRange>27</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>358</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1952"/><citedRange>63</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1954"/><citedRange>749</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:kolver1965"/><citedRange>20</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... including the animals, including the unborn ones ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>231, 232</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:knoll1996"/><citedRange>142, 147, 149</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:kolver1965"/><citedRange>135</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">If a breath comes from my mouth, up to the gods, they give up their negligence ...</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">If a breath comes from my mouth, up to the gods, they give up their negligence …  (cf 172–173)</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>644</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>198</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:kolver1965"/><citedRange>94</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">There is no movement, no word or thought of mine, [not] even within the measure of the smallest moment, which would not be for the happiness of others.</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">There is no movement, no word or thought of mine, [not] even within the measure of the smallest moment, which would not be for the happiness of others.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>259</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>291</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1958a"/><citedRange>158</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1990"/><citedRange>14</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1997"/><citedRange>139</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:kolver1965"/><citedRange>146</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>210</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>250</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1967c"/><citedRange>175</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1997"/><citedRange>139</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1997"/><citedRange>86</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:knoll1996"/><citedRange>56</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... in my own palm ...</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">In allen drei Weltregionen und von allen Lebewesen alles, Geburt, Sinne [und] Schönheiten, sehe ich wie einen Gegenstand in meiner Handfläche.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">In all three regions of the earth and of all living beings, I see all, birth, senses, beauties, like in object in the palm of my hand.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>193</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1968"/><citedRange>228</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1972"/><citedRange>434</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1972"/><ci